The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Harbhajan charged 
                                                Harbhajan charged 
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Harbhajan Singh has been charged under Level 3 of the International Cricket Councils Code of Conduct following an alleged incident that took place on the third day of the second Test at the Sydney Cricket Ground.         
	The charge was laid by umpires Mark Benson and Steve Bucknor after close following a complaint from Australian captain Ricky Ponting, according to a media release.         
	The complaint was made by Ponting after the 116th over of Indias first innings, prior to which Harbhajan is alleged to have made a comment directed at Andrew Symonds.         
	Under the terms of the Code of Conduct, a hearing must take place within 36 hours of the charge being lodged and Match Referee Mike Procter will have the hearing after the close of play on the fourth day.         
	The alleged offence falls under 3.3 of the Code of Conduct, which refers to players or team officials using language or gestures that offends, insults, humiliates, intimidates, threatens, disparages or vilifies another person on the basis of that persons race, religion, gender, colour, descent, or national or ethic origin.         
	If found guilty, Harbhajan could face a ban of between two and four Test matches or between four and eight one-day Internationals.                                                                                                                        
